* Median: The median is the middle value in the sorted dataset. It represents the value below which half of the values fall. The median is more robust to outliers than the mean, as it is less affected by extreme values.
* Mode: The mode is the value that appears most frequently in the dataset. It represents the value that the data is most centered around. If the dataset has multiple values that appear with the same frequency, the dataset has multiple modes.

